730
00:49:16,803 --> 00:49:19,931
It's best if you come on
back down with me right now.

731
00:49:20,140 --> 00:49:21,072
I prefer it.

732
00:49:28,115 --> 00:49:30,379
Be careful. It could be loaded.

733
00:49:30,584 --> 00:49:32,518
-Hold on to that.
-What are you doing?

734
00:49:32,719 --> 00:49:35,620
-Checking this serial number.
-I love my grandchildren.

735
00:49:35,822 --> 00:49:39,724
-A little bit higher.
-It's inappropriate to march in here...

736
00:49:39,993 --> 00:49:42,894
...and you expect me to just let you....

737
00:49:43,096 --> 00:49:44,085
What?

738
00:49:45,332 --> 00:49:47,391
I love you, Caroline.

739
00:49:48,335 --> 00:49:51,361
-You're full of shit.
-I logged it in the evidence locker.

740
00:49:51,571 --> 00:49:53,971
-Logged what in?
-The gun that killed Medgar Evers.

741
00:49:54,174 --> 00:49:55,801
-You're full of shit.
-Who?

742
00:49:56,009 --> 00:49:57,874
He says he found the gun.

743
00:49:58,345 --> 00:50:01,280
-You're full of shit.
-That's something to tell Mrs. Evers.

744
00:50:01,481 --> 00:50:04,075
I'm not gonna tell Mrs. Evers.

745
00:50:05,352 --> 00:50:08,480
You've been making those Friday calls
so she'd trust you.

746
00:50:08,689 --> 00:50:13,592
-lf she finds out....
-I can't have her find out.

747
00:50:13,794 --> 00:50:15,421
This can't leave the office.

748
00:50:15,996 --> 00:50:20,433
The only way we're gonna get a new
indictment is if we find something...

749
00:50:20,634 --> 00:50:23,398
...they didn't have 27 years ago.

750
00:50:23,603 --> 00:50:26,936
The way I see it, that something
will come from Beckwith.

751
00:50:27,140 --> 00:50:29,040
Right now,
he's on his mountaintop...

752
00:50:29,242 --> 00:50:32,234
...shooting his mouth off
to anyone who'll listen.

753
00:50:32,446 --> 00:50:35,813
No telling what incriminating thing's
liable to come out of that man.

754
00:50:36,149 --> 00:50:38,845
But if he knows we have
something like this...

755
00:50:39,052 --> 00:50:41,282
...he'll know we're serious
and clam up.

756
00:50:41,488 --> 00:50:44,514
I doubt that Beckwith and Myrlie
speak all that often.

757
00:50:44,791 --> 00:50:47,089
Myrlie speaks to Jerry Mitchell.

758
00:50:47,594 --> 00:50:50,119
Jerry Mitchell speaks to the world.

759
00:51:01,708 --> 00:51:04,438
"You best stop wasting
our taxpayers' money.

760
00:51:04,644 --> 00:51:06,578
Enjoy your drive home."

761
00:51:07,214 --> 00:51:10,650
Nice to see Jackson still
has some concerned citizens.

762
00:51:12,219 --> 00:51:15,586
Well, heck, son,
what did you expect?

763
00:51:16,089 --> 00:51:19,388
I expect people to act like
decent, law-abiding citizens.

764
00:51:19,593 --> 00:51:21,584
This is 1990, for crying out loud.

765
00:51:21,795 --> 00:51:26,459
Of course it is. And we got blacks
and whites playing ball together...

766
00:51:26,666 --> 00:51:30,762
...and on the police force,
in the government, on TV.

767
00:51:31,171 --> 00:51:35,403
We are a fully evolved society.
Aren't we, son?

768
00:51:38,411 --> 00:51:39,708
Let me tell you something:

769
00:51:40,147 --> 00:51:44,140
This country may be legally
integrated, but emotionally...

770
00:51:44,351 --> 00:51:46,876
...we will always be segregated.

771
00:51:47,087 --> 00:51:49,248
I don't know that I accept that.

772
00:51:49,756 --> 00:51:50,848
Of course not.

773
00:51:51,091 --> 00:51:52,786
You're Bobby DeLaughter...

774
00:51:52,993 --> 00:51:56,019
...Mississippi's self-appointed
new civil rights leader.

775
00:51:56,563 --> 00:51:57,552
Barney...

776
00:51:57,831 --> 00:51:59,628
...do we have to talk about this?

777
00:51:59,833 --> 00:52:02,028
No, we do not.

778
00:52:03,403 --> 00:52:06,395
Who all wants some of your
grandpa's famous baby backs?

779
00:52:06,606 --> 00:52:08,198
I do! I do!

780
00:52:19,052 --> 00:52:20,542
You're my son.

781
00:52:21,021 --> 00:52:22,648
I don't want you to get hurt.

782
00:52:25,559 --> 00:52:27,959
In Jackson, Mississippi

783
00:52:28,962 --> 00:52:32,398
In 1963

784
00:52:33,233 --> 00:52:36,430
There lived a man

785
00:52:36,636 --> 00:52:37,762
Who was brave

786
00:52:39,973 --> 00:52:43,966
He fought for freedom

787
00:52:44,978 --> 00:52:46,309
Hello, Mrs. Evers?

788
00:52:46,613 --> 00:52:47,841
It's Bobby DeLaughter.

789
00:52:48,615 --> 00:52:50,947
Nothing earth shattering, no.

790
00:52:51,284 --> 00:52:53,445
We've located all the witnesses...

791
00:52:53,653 --> 00:52:56,679
...but without the original
trial transcript...

792
00:52:56,890 --> 00:52:58,881
...it's tough piecing the case together.

793
00:53:00,393 --> 00:53:02,224
No, ma'am, that's about it.

794
00:53:03,129 --> 00:53:06,690
-I wish I had more to report.
-Hang up the phone.

795
00:53:06,933 --> 00:53:09,902
-Hang up the phone.
-I hope I'll have something...

796
00:53:10,103 --> 00:53:12,435
...a little more exciting next Friday.

797
00:53:13,273 --> 00:53:14,570
-You too.
-Hang up.

798
00:53:15,175 --> 00:53:17,609
I'll call you next Friday, Mrs. Evers.

799
00:53:18,545 --> 00:53:20,479
Thank you. Goodbye.

800
00:53:20,947 --> 00:53:22,107
What is going on?

801
00:53:22,349 --> 00:53:25,785
Would a confession by Mr. Beckwith
qualify as exciting?

802
00:53:26,620 --> 00:53:27,450
What do you got?

803
00:53:28,221 --> 00:53:29,245
You know Jack Ables?

804
00:53:29,456 --> 00:53:30,286
The lawyer?

805
00:53:30,490 --> 00:53:33,948
He's representing a movie studio
in a defamation of character suit...

806
00:53:34,160 --> 00:53:38,654
...brought by a couple Klansmen.
While he was doing his research...

807
00:53:38,865 --> 00:53:40,526
...he came across that.

808
00:53:42,035 --> 00:53:43,502
"Klandestine."

809
00:53:43,970 --> 00:53:45,597
It was written 20 years ago...

810
00:53:45,805 --> 00:53:49,502
...about this Klan titan turned
FBl informant, Delmar Dennis.

811
00:53:49,709 --> 00:53:54,646
On page 38, he talks about attending
a Klan rally in August of 1965.

812
00:53:54,981 --> 00:53:57,142
Guess who was a motivational speaker?

813
00:53:59,452 --> 00:54:00,942
-Beckwith?
-Our boy.

814
00:54:01,154 --> 00:54:02,382
Listen to this.

815
00:54:02,789 --> 00:54:04,256
And I quote:

816
00:54:04,658 --> 00:54:08,492
" Killing that nigger gave me no more
discomfort than our wives endure...

817
00:54:08,695 --> 00:54:10,686
...when they give birth
to our children."

818
00:54:11,097 --> 00:54:12,860
Sounds like a confession to me.

819
00:54:13,066 --> 00:54:17,332
Let's run down this Delmar Dennis.
We need to have a chat with him.

820
00:54:25,512 --> 00:54:28,106
$100 says old Delmar
chickens out on us.

821
00:54:28,415 --> 00:54:31,851
He's probably hiding in the woods,
shitting in his drawers.

822
00:54:40,327 --> 00:54:42,227
Where the hell is this place?

823
00:54:42,462 --> 00:54:44,327
This guy informed on the Klan.

824
00:54:44,564 --> 00:54:49,126
He could have made a deal with them
to save his butt by delivering us.

825
00:54:49,336 --> 00:54:51,099
That's a happy thought.

826
00:55:57,470 --> 00:55:59,438
One of you Bobby DeLaughter?

827
00:56:01,341 --> 00:56:04,572
Holding rallies and burning
crosses is one thing...

828
00:56:04,778 --> 00:56:08,077
...but when they killed them
three kids up in Neshoba County...

829
00:56:08,281 --> 00:56:10,579
-...freedom riders--
-Goodman, Chaney, Schwerner?

830
00:56:12,285 --> 00:56:15,015
That made a lot of people
come to their senses.

831
00:56:15,422 --> 00:56:19,051
That's why I decided
to go undercover for the FBl.

832
00:56:19,793 --> 00:56:23,092
I need to ask you if what
you say in that book happened.

833
00:56:23,296 --> 00:56:27,392
That part about Beckwith's speech
at that Klan rally. Is that a fact?

834
00:56:28,268 --> 00:56:29,462
It's a fact.

835
00:56:29,836 --> 00:56:33,101
I was shocked, and I remember
thinking how stupid he was...

836
00:56:33,306 --> 00:56:36,298
...shooting off his mouth
like that in front of 100 men.

837
00:56:36,543 --> 00:56:39,444
-Did you report that to the FBl?
-Sure, I did.

838
00:56:39,679 --> 00:56:42,876
But Beckwith was a white man
accused of killing a black.

839
00:56:43,083 --> 00:56:46,746
The FBl wasn't gonna blow my cover
on a case they couldn't win.

840
00:56:46,953 --> 00:56:48,944
They were saving me
for Neshoba because--

841
00:56:49,355 --> 00:56:50,913
Two of the victims were white.

842
00:56:58,164 --> 00:57:01,292
Mr. Dennis,
if I can't build the case...

843
00:57:01,501 --> 00:57:05,232
...I give you my word that
we never had this conversation.

844
00:57:06,239 --> 00:57:07,672
But if I can...

845
00:57:07,874 --> 00:57:09,432
...will you testify?

846
00:57:13,279 --> 00:57:15,543
Byron De La Beckwith
is the craziest...

847
00:57:15,748 --> 00:57:18,876
...most dangerous son of a bitch
I ever come across.

848
00:57:19,185 --> 00:57:21,779
He's so crazy even
the Klan's afraid of him.

849
00:57:22,021 --> 00:57:23,318
He's an old man now.

850
00:57:23,523 --> 00:57:27,960
That old man is probably more dangerous
today than he was 30 years ago.

851
00:57:28,928 --> 00:57:31,488
Mr. Dennis, we need your help.

852
00:57:32,432 --> 00:57:34,662
I can't make no promises.

853
00:57:38,805 --> 00:57:40,705
You know something, Mr. Dennis?

854
00:57:41,141 --> 00:57:42,665
Six months I've worked this case.

855
00:57:42,876 --> 00:57:45,436
A lot of people have told me
to give it up.

856
00:57:45,645 --> 00:57:48,910
" It's 27 years old.
Let sleeping dogs lie."

857
00:57:49,115 --> 00:57:51,549
But I don't see
what difference it makes...

858
00:57:51,751 --> 00:57:53,912
...if a man was
bushwhacked yesterday...

859
00:57:54,120 --> 00:57:57,021
...today or 27 damn years ago.

860
00:57:57,223 --> 00:57:58,884
Murder is murder.

861
00:57:59,626 --> 00:58:02,993
It's still my job to bring
the son of a bitch to justice.

862
00:58:03,196 --> 00:58:04,993
It's still your job to help me.

863
00:58:05,231 --> 00:58:08,598
No. I did my job.
I testified against the Klan.

864
00:58:08,801 --> 00:58:11,201
They shot out my windows,
blew up my car.

865
00:58:11,404 --> 00:58:14,168
They hunted and harassed me
for 25 years!

866
00:58:14,574 --> 00:58:16,701
Don't that get me even
for the wrong I done?

867
00:58:17,977 --> 00:58:20,639
We never get even
for the wrong we've done.

868
00:58:34,394 --> 00:58:36,294
If I do this thing...

869
00:58:38,731 --> 00:58:40,756
...you gotta promise me protection.

870
00:58:50,643 --> 00:58:51,837
What's going on?

871
00:58:53,079 --> 00:58:53,909
Stop that.

872
00:58:54,113 --> 00:58:55,478
Stop that. IKnock it off.

873
00:58:55,715 --> 00:58:56,545
Enough of that!

874
00:58:56,849 --> 00:58:59,317
-What's going on?
-Eddy called you a nigger lover.

875
00:58:59,519 --> 00:59:02,886
My dad says you're after a man
for something that isn't even a crime.

876
00:59:03,122 --> 00:59:06,455
That's enough fighting, son.
You get on home. Go on home.

877
00:59:06,659 --> 00:59:08,092
Let me take a look at you.

878
00:59:08,294 --> 00:59:11,991
My God. Get in this house.
What's gotten into you?

879
00:59:16,569 --> 00:59:19,197
All this fighting.
All this name-calling.

880
00:59:19,706 --> 00:59:21,003
Is this what you want?

881
00:59:21,241 --> 00:59:22,936
To drag your children into this?

882
00:59:23,176 --> 00:59:26,270
What would you have me do?
Let a murderer go free?

883
00:59:26,646 --> 00:59:29,877
I'd never tell you your business.
I'm thinking about the children.

884
00:59:30,083 --> 00:59:33,382
I don't understand why every
decent person in this state...

885
00:59:33,586 --> 00:59:36,783
...isn't sickened by what
happened here 27 years ago.

886
00:59:36,990 --> 00:59:39,254
-Oh, Bobby.
-You're not, are you?

887
00:59:39,459 --> 00:59:41,859
-Not in front of the children.
-Why not?

888
00:59:42,095 --> 00:59:43,528
I was just a kid...

889
00:59:43,730 --> 00:59:46,824
...and I still remember you
and your friends discussing it.

890
00:59:47,033 --> 00:59:50,525
And I recollect someone saying,
"That nigger needed to be shot."

891
00:59:51,804 --> 00:59:53,965
I never said a hateful
thing like that.

892
00:59:54,173 --> 00:59:57,904
-You didn't cry, did you?
-I can't say that I shed any tears--

893
00:59:58,111 --> 01:00:01,672
Had it been our beloved governor,
Ross Barnett, got himself shot...

894
01:00:01,881 --> 01:00:04,611
...you would've been
bawling your eyes out.

895
01:00:04,817 --> 01:00:09,015
Evers left a young widow and three
little kids. Why didn't you cry?

896
01:00:09,222 --> 01:00:11,349
-I don't wanna discuss this now.
-Why?

897
01:00:11,557 --> 01:00:14,048
Because he tried to destroy
our way of life.

898
01:00:14,260 --> 01:00:15,955
And he succeeded all too well.

899
01:00:16,162 --> 01:00:18,926
This state's going to hell
on account of integration.

900
01:00:19,132 --> 01:00:21,930
That's a fact. If you think
they appreciate one thing...

901
01:00:22,135 --> 01:00:23,932
...we gave them, you're crazy.

902
01:00:24,137 --> 01:00:26,628
-Tiger, how do you feel?
-I'm all right.

903
01:00:26,839 --> 01:00:30,331
-Your son has one tough nose.
-So it's not broken?

904
01:00:31,611 --> 01:00:34,705
It'll be tender for a couple days,
then it'll be good as new.

905
01:00:34,981 --> 01:00:36,676
Thank you. I appreciate it.

906
01:00:36,883 --> 01:00:38,282
You're welcome.

907
01:00:39,018 --> 01:00:40,417
Thank you, ma'am.

908
01:00:46,192 --> 01:00:48,592
Are you the one involved
in this Medgar Evers thing?

909
01:00:50,797 --> 01:00:52,230
Yes, I am.

910
01:00:52,765 --> 01:00:56,257
I think what you're trying to do
is very important.

911
01:01:00,373 --> 01:01:02,238
Thank you very much.

912
01:01:17,857 --> 01:01:20,382
I don't want you kids getting
into anymore fights.

913
01:01:20,593 --> 01:01:23,562
-But he called you a--
-I don't care what he called me.

914
01:01:23,763 --> 01:01:27,426
It doesn't bother me. You gotta
learn not to let it bother you.

915
01:01:27,633 --> 01:01:30,796
A lot of people around here
don't like what Daddy's doing now.

916
01:01:31,137 --> 01:01:32,764
What are you doing, Daddy?

917
01:01:34,307 --> 01:01:37,470
I'm trying to put a bad man in jail.

918
01:01:38,044 --> 01:01:39,978
Mama says what you're doing is wrong.

919
01:01:40,179 --> 01:01:43,444
Grandma said Edgar Mevers
is ruining our life.

920
01:01:48,354 --> 01:01:52,120
Medgar Evers was a good guy
who tried to help people.

921
01:01:52,325 --> 01:01:54,885
Did he try to beat the bad guys?

922
01:01:55,094 --> 01:01:58,723
Yes, he did. He fought
so that black people...

923
01:01:58,931 --> 01:02:01,957
...could eat in the same restaurants,
swim in the same pools...

924
01:02:02,168 --> 01:02:05,899
...shop in the same stores and go
to the same schools as white people.

925
01:02:06,105 --> 01:02:07,129
What's wrong with that?

926
01:02:07,340 --> 01:02:08,432
Nothing.

927
01:02:09,575 --> 01:02:12,305
But you'll hear people say
all kinds of bad things...

928
01:02:12,512 --> 01:02:14,173
...about what your daddy's doing.

929
01:02:14,380 --> 01:02:17,315
They're gonna tease you,
try to pick fights.

930
01:02:17,683 --> 01:02:19,446
But no matter what they do...

931
01:02:20,019 --> 01:02:22,180
...I want you to walk away.

932
01:02:23,222 --> 01:02:25,281
What if they say
something really mean?

933
01:02:25,491 --> 01:02:29,086
They're only words. They can't
hurt you unless you let them.

934
01:02:29,295 --> 01:02:31,763
Is this about sticks and stones?

935
01:02:31,964 --> 01:02:34,626
That's exactly what this is about.

936
01:02:34,934 --> 01:02:36,663
Y'all understand what I'm saying?

937
01:02:36,869 --> 01:02:37,961
Yes, sir.

938
01:02:38,304 --> 01:02:39,464
All right.

939
01:02:39,772 --> 01:02:41,171
All y'all get on to bed now.

940
01:02:42,675 --> 01:02:43,869
Good night.

941
01:03:05,998 --> 01:03:09,525
I heard you had a little visit
with my friend Delmar.

942
01:03:09,735 --> 01:03:10,793
Mr. Beckwith?

943
01:03:11,170 --> 01:03:14,731
Next time you see old Delmar,
you tell him for me...

944
01:03:15,007 --> 01:03:17,032
...there are a lot
of dark, winding roads...

945
01:03:17,243 --> 01:03:21,839
... between the backwoods of Louisiana
and a courtroom in Mississippi.

946
01:03:22,415 --> 01:03:25,009
A man could get lost.

947
01:03:34,794 --> 01:03:36,421
Claire, what's the matter?

948
01:03:36,963 --> 01:03:39,056
The ghost's in my room again.

949
01:03:42,935 --> 01:03:44,926
Let's see what we can do.

950
01:03:47,874 --> 01:03:50,104
-Where is he?
-Sitting right there.

951
01:03:50,309 --> 01:03:51,833
Oh, right.

952
01:03:53,546 --> 01:03:55,605
Daddy, sing "Dixie."

953
01:03:57,617 --> 01:03:59,380
Hop into bed, sweetie.

954
01:04:09,929 --> 01:04:11,021
Sing.

955
01:04:12,565 --> 01:04:16,194
You know, sweetie, maybe
" Dixie" is not the right song.

956
01:04:16,669 --> 01:04:19,035
Maybe that's why
this ghost keeps coming back.

957
01:04:19,238 --> 01:04:21,229
-But you said--
-I know, baby.

958
01:04:21,908 --> 01:04:25,275
But I'm not so sure
that all ghosts like "Dixie."

959
01:04:25,478 --> 01:04:28,242
But how do we know
what this ghost likes?

960
01:04:28,814 --> 01:04:33,274
Seeing as this is your special ghost,
maybe he'll like your favorite song.

961
01:04:33,486 --> 01:04:35,078
"Old MacDonald"?

962
01:04:35,288 --> 01:04:36,915
Let's give it a try.

963
01:04:38,925 --> 01:04:40,916
Old MacDonald had a farm

964
01:04:41,193 --> 01:04:42,751
E-I-E-I-O

965
01:04:42,962 --> 01:04:44,896
And on that farm he had a--

966
01:04:45,097 --> 01:04:45,995
What?

967
01:04:46,499 --> 01:04:47,659
A ghost?

968
01:04:49,669 --> 01:04:51,899
And on that farm he had a ghost

969
01:04:52,104 --> 01:04:53,594
E-I-E-I-O

970
01:04:53,940 --> 01:04:55,908
With a boo boo here
And a boo boo there

971
01:04:56,108 --> 01:04:58,736
Here a boo, there a boo
Everywhere a boo boo

972
01:05:12,558 --> 01:05:14,082
You wanted to have lunch
to talk about Burt's nose?

973
01:05:14,860 --> 01:05:16,088
No, actually, l....

974
01:05:16,295 --> 01:05:17,785
I didn't think so.

975
01:05:20,366 --> 01:05:22,197
So then, this is a date?

976
01:05:23,636 --> 01:05:24,762
Apparently.

977
01:05:25,204 --> 01:05:27,001
In the hospital cafeteria?

978
01:05:27,206 --> 01:05:31,643
I took a chance. I thought
it would either be stupid or charming.

979
01:05:32,345 --> 01:05:33,312
What do you think?

980
01:05:33,746 --> 01:05:35,338
Is there a third choice?

981
01:05:35,548 --> 01:05:36,480
Extremely charming?

982
01:05:36,682 --> 01:05:38,206
That's the one.

983
01:05:40,486 --> 01:05:42,215
How'd you get into all this?

984
01:05:42,655 --> 01:05:44,646
You want the standard answer
or the truth?

985
01:05:44,857 --> 01:05:46,381
How about a little of both?

986
01:05:48,394 --> 01:05:50,487
I always liked helping people...

987
01:05:50,696 --> 01:05:51,856
...and I like the hours.

988
01:05:52,131 --> 01:05:53,462
Which answer was that?

989
01:05:53,666 --> 01:05:55,031
A little of both.

990
01:05:55,267 --> 01:05:58,828
But I do like that I work
one week on and one week off.

991
01:05:59,205 --> 01:06:00,365
Can't beat that.

992
01:06:00,573 --> 01:06:03,770
Have to be careful not to shop
too much in that week off.

993
01:06:03,976 --> 01:06:06,570
That can kill you.
What about you?

994
01:06:07,246 --> 01:06:10,044
I wanted to be a lawyer
since I was a little kid.

995
01:06:10,249 --> 01:06:11,876
I watched Perry Mason...

996
01:06:12,084 --> 01:06:15,019
...all the time.
I identified with him.

997
01:06:15,254 --> 01:06:17,722
-But he was a defense attorney.
-I know.

998
01:06:18,190 --> 01:06:21,057
Later, I realized the only way
he ever won a case...

999
01:06:21,260 --> 01:06:23,854
...is if some guy jumped up
and yelled, "I did it!"

1000
01:06:24,063 --> 01:06:27,260
That didn't happen often,
so I switched to the other side.

1001
01:06:27,600 --> 01:06:29,932
I think it's a good thing you did.

1002
01:06:32,538 --> 01:06:34,972
You would be in
the minority these days.

1003
01:06:36,242 --> 01:06:39,439
There are a lot more people
on your side than you think.

1004
01:06:40,546 --> 01:06:43,606
You're not saying that because
I bought you a lime Jell-O?

1005
01:06:44,850 --> 01:06:47,284
Well, it is the way
to a woman's heart.

1006
01:06:49,889 --> 01:06:54,326
But if you could pull this off,
it'd do Mississippi a whole lot of good.

1007
01:06:56,062 --> 01:06:57,290
And if I don't?

1008
01:06:58,898 --> 01:07:01,059
I'll pretend I never met you.

1009
01:07:08,574 --> 01:07:11,509
I have renewed faith
in the institution of marriage.

1010
01:07:11,711 --> 01:07:14,077
I can't get enough
of my hunk of burning love.

1011
01:07:14,280 --> 01:07:16,248
Not now, Clara May!

1012
01:07:18,918 --> 01:07:20,408
Clara Mayfield.

1013
01:07:21,821 --> 01:07:24,415
-It's Jerry Mitchell.
-I'll take it.

1014
01:07:30,496 --> 01:07:33,056
-I know you have the gun.
-We've been over this.

1015
01:07:33,265 --> 01:07:35,563
I know you found it
in Russel Moore's den.

1016
01:07:36,435 --> 01:07:40,895
There'll be a story about how the
D.A. Iied to the people of Jackson...

1017
01:07:41,107 --> 01:07:43,803
...and how Bobby DeLaughter
lied to Myrlie Evers.

1018
01:07:44,009 --> 01:07:46,534
I'm calling to see
if you care to comment.

1019
01:07:46,746 --> 01:07:48,577
You've explained why
you lied to the press.

1020
01:07:48,781 --> 01:07:51,306
You still have not explained
why you lied to me.

1021
01:07:51,517 --> 01:07:54,077
I told you. Jerry Mitchell
is a loose cannon.

1022
01:07:54,286 --> 01:07:57,255
This case was so delicate,
I didn't want to take chances.

1023
01:07:57,456 --> 01:08:01,449
I'm the last person on earth who
would jeopardize this investigation.

1024
01:08:01,660 --> 01:08:04,094
There's something
you're not telling me.

1025
01:08:04,296 --> 01:08:07,163
I swear to God, there is no cover-up.

1026
01:08:07,366 --> 01:08:10,426
You fully intend to seek
an indictment and a new trial?

1027
01:08:10,636 --> 01:08:12,831
That's what we've
been working toward.

1028
01:08:13,038 --> 01:08:15,131
I thought so, Mr. DeLaughter.

1029
01:08:15,541 --> 01:08:16,974
I thought so.

1030
01:08:17,276 --> 01:08:20,837
This latest revelation only proves
what we've suspected all along.

1031
01:08:21,046 --> 01:08:25,107
Peters and DeLaughter are just putting
on a show for the black community.

1032
01:08:25,317 --> 01:08:29,344
As far as I'm concerned, they're nothing
but a pair of lying racists...

1033
01:08:29,555 --> 01:08:31,182
...who never, I repeat, never...

1034
01:08:31,390 --> 01:08:34,359
...had any intention
of prosecuting this case.

1035
01:08:36,395 --> 01:08:37,555
You wanted to see me?

1036
01:08:37,763 --> 01:08:39,663
Come on, sit down.

1037
01:08:42,501 --> 01:08:46,562
You don't mind being seen in
the same room with a "lying racist"?

1038
01:08:47,373 --> 01:08:49,170
I don't mind if you don't.

1039
01:08:50,843 --> 01:08:52,208
You know Pat Bennett?

1040
01:08:52,745 --> 01:08:55,680
Sure, she's one of the best
lawyers in the state.

1041
01:08:57,183 --> 01:08:58,707
Why are we talking about her?

1042
01:09:00,019 --> 01:09:03,182
I thought she might be able
to help you on the case.

1043
01:09:04,089 --> 01:09:06,353
I've got it under control, Ed.

1044
01:09:08,761 --> 01:09:11,389
You have your share of
the 93 capital murder cases...

1045
01:09:11,597 --> 01:09:13,929
...we have waiting for trial
under control?

1046
01:09:14,700 --> 01:09:16,998
What new excuse would
you suggest I give...

1047
01:09:17,203 --> 01:09:20,502
...to the families as to why those
who've murdered their loved ones...

1048
01:09:20,706 --> 01:09:22,435
...have yet to see a courtroom?

1049
01:09:23,108 --> 01:09:26,703
I'm just curious.
The fact that Pat Bennett is black...

1050
01:09:26,912 --> 01:09:29,574
...wouldn't have anything to do
with this, would it?

1051
01:09:30,316 --> 01:09:32,477
I'm not gonna dignify that.

1052
01:09:34,486 --> 01:09:37,978
Whatever you may think,
this is not the Bobby DeLaughter case.

1053
01:09:38,190 --> 01:09:41,626
This is a case against the peace
and dignity of Mississippi.

1054
01:09:42,561 --> 01:09:44,995
Monday morning, I'm making a change.

1055
01:09:50,102 --> 01:09:53,503
You're about to hear the testimony
of a fingerprint expert...

1056
01:09:53,706 --> 01:09:58,006
...concerning evidence he claims
to have identified in a certain glass.

1057
01:09:58,210 --> 01:09:59,871
You're entitled to consider...

1058
01:10:00,079 --> 01:10:03,913
... the prosecution's failure to make
the glass available to the defense.

1059
01:10:04,116 --> 01:10:08,644
It is permissible that for one fact
alone to raise a doubt in your minds...

1060
01:10:08,854 --> 01:10:11,254
... that will require
Mrs. Savage's acquittal.

1061
01:10:11,457 --> 01:10:14,790
-Can he do that?
-This is my case, damn it.

1062
01:10:14,994 --> 01:10:17,019
How dare they say
I'm putting on a show?

1063
01:10:17,229 --> 01:10:20,596
Only two people care about
this case, and I'm one of them.

1064
01:10:20,799 --> 01:10:24,565
If anybody's putting on a show,
they are. The only thing they' re--

1065
01:10:25,237 --> 01:10:28,764
They're only trying to stir up
emotions and position themselves...

1066
01:10:28,974 --> 01:10:31,408
...as the saviors
of the black community.

1067
01:10:39,518 --> 01:10:40,678
Where you going?

1068
01:10:59,872 --> 01:11:02,670
This is Bobby DeLaughter.
I hope I didn't disturb you.

1069
01:11:04,343 --> 01:11:06,436
This won't take but a minute, ma'am.

1070
01:11:07,846 --> 01:11:10,076
When I started off,
I had nothing more than...

1071
01:11:10,282 --> 01:11:13,274
...a couple of pages
in an old police report.

1072
01:11:14,053 --> 01:11:17,216
I spent the better part of a year
bumping up against dead witnesses...

1073
01:11:17,423 --> 01:11:19,414
...and tracking down live ones.

1074
01:11:19,625 --> 01:11:22,958
My car's been vandalized,
my son's been in a fight...

1075
01:11:23,162 --> 01:11:26,757
...and I've been called ugly things
by every racist in Mississippi.

1076
01:11:26,966 --> 01:11:29,059
Now, when there's a chance
for an indictment...

1077
01:11:29,268 --> 01:11:31,429
...I've gotta fight off
black politicians too.

1078
01:11:31,637 --> 01:11:35,767
I'm sorry I lied about the gun,
but I've made a commitment to this case.

1079
01:11:35,975 --> 01:11:37,169
I'll be goddamned--

1080
01:11:37,376 --> 01:11:40,209
Pardon me, if I give it up
to some special prosecutor...

1081
01:11:40,412 --> 01:11:42,812
...I don't care if he's
black, green or blue.

1082
01:11:43,015 --> 01:11:46,075
I'm committed and I'm asking you
to make a commitment to me.

1083
01:11:46,285 --> 01:11:49,015
If you do, I'll ride this thing
to the finish line...

1084
01:11:49,221 --> 01:11:51,485
...or collapse
heading in that direction.

1085
01:11:53,058 --> 01:11:55,686
Thank you for your call,
Mr. DeLaughter.

1086
01:12:00,132 --> 01:12:02,532
The hell with her!
She's like all the rest.

1087
01:12:02,735 --> 01:12:06,865
The white world hasn't gone out
of its way to make her trusting.

1088
01:12:07,072 --> 01:12:08,937
When does it start?
What do I have to do?

1089
01:12:09,141 --> 01:12:12,133
We had a real chance to send
a message to this country...

1090
01:12:12,344 --> 01:12:15,313
...that Mississippi isn't
a bunch of redneck racists.

1091
01:12:15,514 --> 01:12:19,610
My mother was right. We should
separate and let the South rise again.

1092
01:12:19,818 --> 01:12:21,945
-You don't believe that.
-Why not?

1093
01:12:22,154 --> 01:12:23,644
She doesn't want my help.

1094
01:12:23,856 --> 01:12:26,290
I'm just another white man
putting her in her place.

1095
01:12:26,492 --> 01:12:28,983
She sees no difference
between me and Beckwith.

1096
01:12:29,194 --> 01:12:31,094
-You didn't tell her about the gun.
-Right.

1097
01:12:31,363 --> 01:12:35,390
If I had it to do over again,
I still wouldn't have told her.

1098
01:12:35,601 --> 01:12:39,560
IKeeping the discovery of the murder
weapon a secret was a good strategy.

1099
01:12:39,772 --> 01:12:43,902
It wouldn't bother her a lick if I was
black. I'd just be a smart lawyer.

1100
01:12:44,543 --> 01:12:46,738
You can't have it both ways.

1101
01:12:47,079 --> 01:12:48,808
What do you mean by that?

1102
01:12:50,382 --> 01:12:53,078
You said the reason you didn't
tell her about the gun...

1103
01:12:53,285 --> 01:12:55,913
...was that you were afraid
she would leak the story.

1104
01:12:56,121 --> 01:12:59,215
You can't expect her to trust you,
if you don't trust her.

1105
01:13:17,409 --> 01:13:20,640
I want you to meet with Pat Bennett
and bring her up to speed.

1106
01:13:22,448 --> 01:13:23,472
Fine.

1107
01:13:24,817 --> 01:13:26,250
It's for the best.

1108
01:13:27,386 --> 01:13:28,978
If you say so.

1109
01:13:51,977 --> 01:13:53,968
I'm going out.
You want something?

1110
01:13:54,179 --> 01:13:57,910
I'd like a Mercedes convertible,
but I'd settle for a Dr. Pepper.

1111
01:14:53,438 --> 01:14:56,839
There are four important
things in my life:

1112
01:14:57,743 --> 01:14:59,870
Medgar, Walter...

1113
01:15:00,179 --> 01:15:01,544
...my children...

1114
01:15:01,847 --> 01:15:03,246
...and this...

1115
01:15:03,882 --> 01:15:07,181
...the original
court-certified transcript.

1116
01:15:07,753 --> 01:15:10,313
I've kept this for 27 years...

1117
01:15:10,622 --> 01:15:12,886
...through three district attorneys.

1118
01:15:13,091 --> 01:15:14,991
Once I give this up...

1119
01:15:15,194 --> 01:15:18,061
...I know that it may be gone forever.

1120
01:15:27,706 --> 01:15:30,266
I don't believe you'll find
anymore opposition...

1121
01:15:30,475 --> 01:15:32,966
...to your continuing
to handle this case.

1122
01:15:34,279 --> 01:15:35,541
Thank you, ma'am.

1123
01:15:38,450 --> 01:15:40,543
It's truly appreciated.

1124
01:15:41,520 --> 01:15:43,784
Let's get the son of a bitch.

1125
01:15:45,057 --> 01:15:46,456
My pleasure.

1126
01:15:48,594 --> 01:15:50,687
The decision by the D.A.'s office...

1127
01:15:50,896 --> 01:15:54,855
...to re-open the 27-year-old murder
case of Byron De La Beckwith...

1128
01:15:55,067 --> 01:15:56,728
...continues to cause controversy.

1129
01:15:57,069 --> 01:16:00,004
Citizens of Jackson are concerned...

1130
01:16:00,205 --> 01:16:03,504
... that taxpayers' money is being
used to dig up the past.

1131
01:16:03,709 --> 01:16:07,440
The grand jury handed down an
indictment of Byron De La Beckwith...

1132
01:16:07,646 --> 01:16:10,638
...in the murder of
civil rights leader Medgar Evers.

1133
01:16:10,849 --> 01:16:12,373
Extradition in the Beckwith case...

1134
01:16:12,584 --> 01:16:15,815
...is seen as a stumbling
block for the D.A.'s office.

1135
01:16:16,021 --> 01:16:18,387
I plan to fight repossession--
What's the word?

1136
01:16:18,590 --> 01:16:21,753
Extradition tooth, nail and claw!

1137
01:16:22,294 --> 01:16:25,286
In an attempt to replace
a lost autopsy report...

1138
01:16:25,497 --> 01:16:29,263
... the D.A.'s office of Hinds County
today received permission...

1139
01:16:29,468 --> 01:16:31,561
...by the Evers family
to exhume the body...

1140
01:16:31,770 --> 01:16:35,206
...of slain civil rights leader
Medgar Evers.

1141
01:16:35,874 --> 01:16:39,401
The body, buried in
Arlington National Cemetery in 1963...

1142
01:16:39,611 --> 01:16:42,273
... was found in remarkably
near-perfect condition.

1143
01:16:46,385 --> 01:16:49,411
After 18 months, extradition was
finally granted...

1144
01:16:49,621 --> 01:16:51,589
...in the case
of Byron De La Beckwith...

1145
01:16:51,790 --> 01:16:55,658
... the man accused of slaying
civil rights leader Medgar Evers.

1146
01:16:56,728 --> 01:17:01,256
Beckwith will face murder charges
30 years after the initial two trials...

1147
01:17:01,466 --> 01:17:04,594
...for the same offense
ended in hung juries.

1148
01:17:04,803 --> 01:17:05,667
Thank you, son.

1149
01:17:05,971 --> 01:17:07,666
" I first received the call...

1150
01:17:07,873 --> 01:17:09,807
...at 9 :42 p. m...

1151
01:17:10,008 --> 01:17:13,705
...on the night of June 12, 1963.

1152
01:17:15,480 --> 01:17:18,108
My partner and I responded
and proceeded to the crime scene...

1153
01:17:18,317 --> 01:17:21,650
...Iocated at 2332 Guynes Street."

1154
01:17:21,987 --> 01:17:23,648
That's pretty good, Benny...

1155
01:17:23,855 --> 01:17:26,790
...but just because you read
the part of a dead witness...

1156
01:17:26,992 --> 01:17:29,893
...doesn't mean you have to
act like you're actually dead.

1157
01:17:30,095 --> 01:17:31,494
I'm doing my best.

1158
01:17:31,697 --> 01:17:33,164
I know you are.

1159
01:17:33,365 --> 01:17:35,856
Medgar Evers' autopsy report
just came in.

1160
01:17:36,501 --> 01:17:39,834
You're not gonna believe this.
He's still dead.

1161
01:17:40,305 --> 01:17:41,499
Thank you, Clara.

1162
01:17:41,707 --> 01:17:45,165
I got off the phone with Charles Evers.
He won't come to the trial.

1163
01:17:45,377 --> 01:17:46,207
Did he say why?

1164
01:17:46,411 --> 01:17:47,673
He wouldn't say.

1165
01:17:47,879 --> 01:17:50,177
Get me the address
of his radio station.

1166
01:17:50,382 --> 01:17:52,543
They found a bullet fragment
in the body.

1167
01:17:52,751 --> 01:17:55,276
It's consistent with a.30-06 Enfield.

1168
01:17:56,254 --> 01:18:00,190
You'll be sorry. What happened to
that nigger will happen to you.

1169
01:18:01,560 --> 01:18:02,390
Another one?

1170
01:18:04,229 --> 01:18:08,256
Closer we get to trial, the more
nutjobs will crawl out of the woodwork.

1171
01:18:09,468 --> 01:18:10,366
You got a gun?

1172
01:18:11,903 --> 01:18:13,530
Here. T ake this.

1173
01:18:14,072 --> 01:18:15,937
No, wait. T ake this.

1174
01:18:17,576 --> 01:18:19,168
T ake this.

1175
01:18:43,502 --> 01:18:46,938
That was Muddy Waters doing
his thing for y'all.

1176
01:18:47,139 --> 01:18:50,131
Now I'll play a little something
that goes way back.

1177
01:18:50,342 --> 01:18:53,311
The great Robert Johnson.

1178
01:18:57,749 --> 01:18:58,807
Mr. Evers?

1179
01:19:02,187 --> 01:19:04,655
-Hi, I'm--
-Bobby DeLaughter.

1180
01:19:06,091 --> 01:19:07,820
Please sit down.

1181
01:19:17,669 --> 01:19:19,000
Robert Johnson.

1182
01:19:19,504 --> 01:19:21,734
IKing of the Delta Blues.

1183
01:19:24,576 --> 01:19:26,908
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

1184
01:19:29,481 --> 01:19:31,608
May your soul rise up to heaven...

1185
01:19:31,817 --> 01:19:34,285
...'fore the devil knows you're dead.

1186
01:19:40,792 --> 01:19:45,491
They say Robert Johnson sold his soul to
the devil to play the guitar like that.

1187
01:19:45,897 --> 01:19:46,795
What do you think?

1188
01:19:46,998 --> 01:19:51,298
If the devil wanted my soul, it'd cost
a lot more than some guitar lessons.

1189
01:19:54,539 --> 01:19:57,030
I believe after this trial's over...

1190
01:19:57,242 --> 01:19:59,676
...Mississippi come through this time.

1191
01:19:59,978 --> 01:20:02,845
That's why I came here
to talk with you, Mr. Evers.

1192
01:20:03,048 --> 01:20:06,916
Would you change your mind and come
to the trial? Your presence...

1193
01:20:07,118 --> 01:20:09,052
...would mean a great deal.

1194
01:20:10,889 --> 01:20:13,289
Let me tell you something.

1195
01:20:14,559 --> 01:20:17,050
Medgar was my baby brother.

1196
01:20:17,696 --> 01:20:20,460
There ain't nothing
I wouldn't do for him.

1197
01:20:21,533 --> 01:20:23,262
When we were little kids...

1198
01:20:23,468 --> 01:20:25,231
...we used to sleep in the same bed.

1199
01:20:25,437 --> 01:20:26,836
And on cold nights...

1200
01:20:27,038 --> 01:20:30,667
...I'd climb in first just so I could
warm up the sheets for him.

1201
01:20:33,245 --> 01:20:36,578
I didn't go to the first two trials.

1202
01:20:37,883 --> 01:20:39,407
Myrlie...

1203
01:20:40,085 --> 01:20:43,486
...a lot of people,
they criticized me for that.

1204
01:20:44,289 --> 01:20:46,917
But I won't go
to no third trial neither...

1205
01:20:47,959 --> 01:20:50,553
...and for the exact same reason.

1206
01:20:50,762 --> 01:20:54,789
I know if I ever got in the same room
with Byron De La Beckwith...

1207
01:20:55,000 --> 01:20:57,434
...as God is my witness...

1208
01:20:57,769 --> 01:21:01,261
...I'd wrap my hands around
his chicken neck and snap it in half.

1209
01:21:01,473 --> 01:21:03,202
And nobody...

1210
01:21:03,408 --> 01:21:05,342
...be able to stop me.

1211
01:21:07,012 --> 01:21:08,639
I wouldn't blame you.

1212
01:21:08,847 --> 01:21:10,075
Nobody hardly ever...

1213
01:21:10,282 --> 01:21:12,682
...remembers Medgar anymore.

1214
01:21:13,652 --> 01:21:15,517
Whites or blacks.

1215
01:21:16,187 --> 01:21:18,519
And that's a goddamn shame.

1216
01:21:19,257 --> 01:21:22,090
Because whatever rights
the black man has now...

1217
01:21:22,294 --> 01:21:25,627
...he's got because of something
called the Civil Rights Movement.

1218
01:21:25,830 --> 01:21:28,958
And for a long time here
in the state of Mississippi...

1219
01:21:29,467 --> 01:21:33,267
...before the television, newspapers,
back before the fancy speeches...

1220
01:21:33,471 --> 01:21:37,464
...my brother, Medgar, was
the Civil Rights Movement.

1221
01:21:43,114 --> 01:21:47,608
I'm sitting here tonight,
talking to my friend and your friend...

1222
01:21:47,819 --> 01:21:50,481
...Assistant District Attorney
Bobby DeLaughter.

1223
01:21:50,689 --> 01:21:53,817
We're talking about my brother,
Medgar Evers...

1224
01:21:54,025 --> 01:21:58,826
...and we're gonna play the blues
for Medgar all night long.

1225
01:22:09,341 --> 01:22:11,502
You and my sister-in-law...

1226
01:22:12,611 --> 01:22:14,545
...you get justice for my brother.

1227
01:22:24,322 --> 01:22:26,517
Devil, if you listening...

1228
01:22:26,758 --> 01:22:29,056
...I won't sell my soul
for no guitar lessons...

1229
01:22:29,260 --> 01:22:31,694
...but I'll sell my soul for that.

1230
01:22:36,334 --> 01:22:38,199
Are you surprised bail
was granted so quickly?

1231
01:22:38,403 --> 01:22:41,201
Mr. Beckwith was being held
as a political prisoner.

1232
01:22:41,406 --> 01:22:44,569
He's not been found guilty.
Why should he be kept in jail?

1233
01:22:45,944 --> 01:22:48,435
Mr. Scott, you're an officer
of the Nationalist Movement, correct?

1234
01:22:48,647 --> 01:22:50,979
Is that where the money came from
to secure his bond?

1235
01:22:51,182 --> 01:22:55,414
Mr. Beckwith has a lot of friends here.
We'll do whatever it takes.

1236
01:22:55,887 --> 01:23:00,119
Suppose he doesn't show for the trial?
Suppose he leaves the country?

1237
01:23:00,325 --> 01:23:02,384
If he runs, we'll find him.

1238
01:23:02,594 --> 01:23:04,323
How long will that take?

1239
01:23:04,529 --> 01:23:07,327
Another five years? Another 10?

1240
01:23:07,532 --> 01:23:11,559
I've already devoted a lifetime to this.
That ought to be enough.

1241
01:23:12,537 --> 01:23:15,062
Yes, ma'am. It sure ought to be.

1242
01:23:20,011 --> 01:23:21,638
I'm sorry, Bobby.

1243
01:23:22,747 --> 01:23:24,738
It's all right, Mrs. Evers.

1244
01:23:24,949 --> 01:23:26,439
It's quite all right.

1245
01:23:53,511 --> 01:23:56,071
-How's Jared doing?
-Fine.

1246
01:23:56,281 --> 01:23:59,546
He and Burt seem like
they've been brothers all their lives.

1247
01:23:59,751 --> 01:24:01,275
They all sleeping?

1248
01:24:02,954 --> 01:24:05,184
And that's what you should be doing.

1249
01:24:06,024 --> 01:24:08,219
I want the opening statement
to be great.

1250
01:24:08,993 --> 01:24:11,393
It was great when you read
it three nights ago.

1251
01:24:11,596 --> 01:24:13,530
Unless you snuck in something about...

1252
01:24:13,732 --> 01:24:15,825
...Beckwith deserving
the Nobel Peace Prize...

1253
01:24:16,034 --> 01:24:18,264
...I'm sure it'll be great
tomorrow morning.

1254
01:24:18,470 --> 01:24:20,995
You see? That's why I look to you.

1255
01:24:21,206 --> 01:24:24,664
Eliminate Nobel Peace Prize reference.

1256
01:24:24,876 --> 01:24:26,343
That's good.

1257
01:24:28,680 --> 01:24:32,946
I left a gift for you in appreciation
for everything you're doing...

1258
01:24:33,151 --> 01:24:35,016
... to ruin civilized society.

1259
01:24:35,220 --> 01:24:38,451
-What the hell is this?
-It's scheduled to go off at 10 p.m.

1260
01:24:38,656 --> 01:24:40,647
You have a nice night.

1261
01:24:45,163 --> 01:24:45,993
It's a bomb.

1262
01:24:51,002 --> 01:24:52,799
Everybody, get up.
Let's go.

1263
01:24:53,004 --> 01:24:54,369
What's going on?

1264
01:24:54,572 --> 01:24:58,474
It's nothing at all. Outside that door.
A little drill is all.

1265
01:24:58,676 --> 01:25:00,268
Head for the front door.

1266
01:25:34,412 --> 01:25:36,573
Is this still the drill?

1267
01:25:49,694 --> 01:25:51,252
Where are we going, Dad?

1268
01:25:51,462 --> 01:25:53,589
Told you we're going
to the Holiday Inn.

1269
01:25:53,798 --> 01:25:56,232
Is that where we're going?
The Holiday Inn?

1270
01:25:56,434 --> 01:25:57,332
That's right.

1271
01:25:57,535 --> 01:26:01,869
We haven't found anything,
but we'll go through it one more time.

1272
01:26:02,073 --> 01:26:03,904
I appreciate that.

1273
01:26:24,162 --> 01:26:28,758
I told them if anything ever happened,
all they had to do was walk away.

1274
01:26:30,935 --> 01:26:34,098
How're they supposed to walk away
from a bomb?

1275
01:26:39,077 --> 01:26:41,011
There wasn't a bomb.

1276
01:26:43,548 --> 01:26:45,015
This time.

1277
01:26:48,553 --> 01:26:51,420
If you want to give this thing up,
I understand.

1278
01:26:51,623 --> 01:26:55,150
No one could fault you. But the world
isn't going to be any safer.

1279
01:26:55,360 --> 01:26:58,227
I don't give a shit about the world.
These are my children.

1280
01:26:58,429 --> 01:26:59,760
Yes, they are.

1281
01:26:59,964 --> 01:27:02,455
Someday they'll be able
to tell their children...

1282
01:27:02,667 --> 01:27:05,397
...that their daddy put away
Medgar Evers' killer.

1283
01:27:05,970 --> 01:27:08,905
Medgar Evers was a fool,
and my daddy was right.

1284
01:27:09,107 --> 01:27:11,405
Doesn't matter how many
civil rights laws you pass.

1285
01:27:11,609 --> 01:27:13,907
You'll never legislate
how people think.

1286
01:27:14,112 --> 01:27:16,774
There are always gonna be
a few misguided people.

1287
01:27:16,981 --> 01:27:21,077
I'm not talking about a few people.
I'm talking about everybody, about us.

1288
01:27:21,286 --> 01:27:23,754
Do we have one single
black friend? No.

1289
01:27:23,955 --> 01:27:26,423
We don't have dinner with them
or have them over.

1290
01:27:26,624 --> 01:27:28,251
We don't sit with them in church.

1291
01:27:28,459 --> 01:27:31,257
You think this one trial will
magically change this?

1292
01:27:31,496 --> 01:27:33,157
No, I don't.

1293
01:27:33,631 --> 01:27:35,155
It's a step.

1294
01:27:35,900 --> 01:27:37,925
That's all anyone can do
is take a step.

1295
01:27:38,136 --> 01:27:40,263
Why do I have to take that step?

1296
01:27:40,471 --> 01:27:43,406
So some sick son of a bitch
can murder my wife and kids?

1297
01:27:43,608 --> 01:27:46,270
Excuse me if I'm not interested
in taking that step.

1298
01:27:46,477 --> 01:27:47,671
Where are you going?

1299
01:27:47,879 --> 01:27:49,642
For a drive.

1300
01:30:01,913 --> 01:30:06,282
" I don't know if I'm going to heaven
or hell, but I'm going from Jackson."

1301
01:30:09,320 --> 01:30:13,984
We're on record in the matter
of Mississippi v. Byron De La Beckwith.

1302
01:30:14,192 --> 01:30:16,319
Does prosecution have
its opening statement?

1303
01:30:17,829 --> 01:30:18,796
We do, Your Honor.

1304
01:30:25,036 --> 01:30:26,901
Ladies and gentlemen...

1305
01:30:27,105 --> 01:30:29,596
...this is a very simple case.

1306
01:30:31,576 --> 01:30:34,238
It's about a man whose life
was snuffed out...

1307
01:30:34,445 --> 01:30:37,812
...on June the 12th of 1963...

1308
01:30:38,416 --> 01:30:41,146
...by a bullet that tore
through his body.

1309
01:30:41,786 --> 01:30:44,721
A bullet aimed out of prejudice...

1310
01:30:44,922 --> 01:30:46,787
...propelled by hatred...

1311
01:30:46,991 --> 01:30:50,427
...and fired by
a back-shooting coward...

1312
01:30:51,562 --> 01:30:53,257
...from ambush...

1313
01:30:54,398 --> 01:30:55,490
...at night.

1314
01:30:56,033 --> 01:31:00,868
The evidence will overwhelmingly show
that Byron De La Beckwith...

1315
01:31:01,339 --> 01:31:04,775
...a self-proclaimed, rabid racist
on a lifelong mission...

1316
01:31:04,976 --> 01:31:07,774
...to purge society
of anyone and anything...

1317
01:31:07,979 --> 01:31:09,606
...that stood for integration...

1318
01:31:09,814 --> 01:31:12,339
...is the man that fired that bullet.

1319
01:31:12,917 --> 01:31:16,182
Evidence will show how, when he
thought he beat the system...

1320
01:31:16,387 --> 01:31:18,981
...he bragged about what he'd done.

1321
01:31:20,024 --> 01:31:23,391
Bragged about getting
away with murder.

1322
01:31:25,463 --> 01:31:29,593
The evidence will undeniably show that
the person who pulled the trigger...

1323
01:31:29,800 --> 01:31:33,827
...and ended the life of Medgar Evers
is this defendant...

1324
01:31:34,672 --> 01:31:36,731
...Byron De La Beckwith.

1325
01:31:41,245 --> 01:31:42,712
Mr. Coxwell?

1326
01:31:43,748 --> 01:31:45,340
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen.

1327
01:31:45,783 --> 01:31:49,514
My name is Merrida Coxwell.
This is James Kitchens...

1328
01:31:49,720 --> 01:31:52,951
...and we are representing
Mr. Beckwith.

1329
01:31:53,558 --> 01:31:56,288
Mr. DeLaughter started
his opening statement...

1330
01:31:56,494 --> 01:31:59,463
...by saying that this was
a very simple case.

1331
01:31:59,664 --> 01:32:01,131
I agree with him.

1332
01:32:01,399 --> 01:32:05,392
But what Mr. DeLaughter is going
to rely on is for you...

1333
01:32:05,603 --> 01:32:10,199
...to convict Mr. Beckwith
simply because of his opinions.

1334
01:32:10,808 --> 01:32:11,968
That's because...

1335
01:32:12,176 --> 01:32:16,636
...he knows that the state cannot prove
to you beyond a reasonable doubt...

1336
01:32:16,847 --> 01:32:19,407
...that the defendant committed
the crime.

1337
01:32:19,617 --> 01:32:21,949
By the time this trial is over...

1338
01:32:22,153 --> 01:32:25,816
...you will have seen it was
physically impossible...

1339
01:32:26,023 --> 01:32:29,117
...for Mr. Byron De La Beckwith
to have killed Medgar Evers.

1340
01:32:29,460 --> 01:32:31,860
Mr. Beckwith is not guilty.

1341
01:32:32,063 --> 01:32:34,395
That's what the proof will show.

1342
01:32:34,999 --> 01:32:36,227
Thank you.

1343
01:32:38,135 --> 01:32:40,126
The state may call its first witness.

1344
01:32:41,405 --> 01:32:43,896
The state calls Myrlie Evers.

1345
01:32:56,887 --> 01:32:58,252
Raise your right hand.

1346
01:32:58,456 --> 01:33:00,481
Do you swear to tell the truth...

1347
01:33:00,691 --> 01:33:03,455
-...the whole truth, so help you God?
-I do.

1348
01:33:03,728 --> 01:33:05,025
Be seated.

1349
01:33:11,269 --> 01:33:13,032
Will you tell us your name?

1350
01:33:13,604 --> 01:33:15,697
My name is Myrlie Evers.

1351
01:33:15,906 --> 01:33:19,000
Going back to 1963,
were you married at that time?

1352
01:33:19,210 --> 01:33:20,643
Yes, I was.

1353
01:33:20,845 --> 01:33:22,676
And to whom were you married?

1354
01:33:25,416 --> 01:33:27,281
Medgar Wylie...

1355
01:33:27,485 --> 01:33:28,975
...Evers.

1356
01:33:35,293 --> 01:33:38,285
When was the last time
you saw your husband alive?

1357
01:33:39,163 --> 01:33:41,859
June 11, 1963.

1358
01:33:43,534 --> 01:33:45,593
I'd fallen behind...

1359
01:33:45,803 --> 01:33:48,966
...in my housework
and got up early that morning...

1360
01:33:49,240 --> 01:33:51,731
...to iron some shirts for Medgar.

1361
01:33:53,110 --> 01:33:54,600
By the time he woke...

1362
01:33:54,812 --> 01:33:59,146
...I had 10 freshly ironed shirts
neatly hung on hangers.

1363
01:34:00,685 --> 01:34:03,950
He said, "I thank you
for ironing these shirts...

1364
01:34:04,155 --> 01:34:05,918
...but I'm not going to need them."

1365
01:34:07,358 --> 01:34:11,351
Before he left for work that morning,
he kissed us all goodbye...

1366
01:34:11,762 --> 01:34:13,662
...and then left.

1367
01:34:15,032 --> 01:34:16,624
But then he came back...

1368
01:34:16,834 --> 01:34:18,927
...and took me aside.

1369
01:34:19,337 --> 01:34:21,828
He said, "If anything
should happen to me...

1370
01:34:22,039 --> 01:34:24,098
...I want you to promise me...

1371
01:34:24,308 --> 01:34:27,004
...you will take care of my babies."

1372
01:34:27,945 --> 01:34:31,312
I said, "Of course.
They're my babies too."

1373
01:34:33,751 --> 01:34:37,346
He then kissed us all
goodbye again and left.

1374
01:34:40,358 --> 01:34:42,758
Could you tell the jury
what you remember...

1375
01:34:42,960 --> 01:34:46,919
...seeing and hearing when your husband
returned home that night?

1376
01:34:47,598 --> 01:34:51,125
It was just after midnight
when he got home.

1377
01:34:51,969 --> 01:34:53,800
We heard the car.

1378
01:35:02,246 --> 01:35:04,714
And then there was...

1379
01:35:09,053 --> 01:35:11,647
...this horrible blast.

1380
01:35:14,191 --> 01:35:15,818
The children...

1381
01:35:16,527 --> 01:35:19,758
...fell to the floor
as their father had taught them.

1382
01:35:20,765 --> 01:35:23,325
I bolted to the front door.

1383
01:35:24,702 --> 01:35:27,569
Medgar was lying in the carport.

1384
01:35:28,806 --> 01:35:31,331
He still had his keys in his hand.

1385
01:35:33,544 --> 01:35:35,910
Blood everywhere.

1386
01:35:37,648 --> 01:35:40,276
The children came out
shortly after I did...

1387
01:35:40,484 --> 01:35:42,349
...and they were screaming...

1388
01:35:43,354 --> 01:35:44,514
... "Daddy!

1389
01:35:45,556 --> 01:35:47,080
Daddy, get up!

1390
01:35:48,893 --> 01:35:50,861
Daddy, please get up."

1391
01:35:54,465 --> 01:35:57,366
But I knew he would
never get up again.

1392
01:36:02,373 --> 01:36:04,273
Nothing further, Your Honor.

1393
01:36:06,377 --> 01:36:11,440
Mr. McIntyre, have you ever owned
a 1917 Enfield.30-06 rifle?

1394
01:36:12,249 --> 01:36:13,443
Yes, I have.

1395
01:36:13,651 --> 01:36:16,381
Did you own that rifle in 1963?

1396
01:36:17,321 --> 01:36:22,122
Sometime, I believe in 1960,
I traded it to Mr. Beckwith.

1397
01:36:22,393 --> 01:36:26,454
Mr. McIntyre, I want to show you
this firearm and ask if you would...

1398
01:36:26,664 --> 01:36:29,895
...read the serial number
on the barrel, please.

1399
01:36:30,601 --> 01:36:34,537
1-0-5-2-6-8-2.

1400
01:36:34,738 --> 01:36:38,799
Thank you. Going back to exhibit 35,
would you read the serial number...

1401
01:36:39,009 --> 01:36:41,477
...on the invoice of the gun
that you purchased...

1402
01:36:41,679 --> 01:36:43,738
...and later traded to Mr. Beckwith?

1403
01:36:43,948 --> 01:36:47,611
1-0-5-2-6-8-2.

1404
01:36:48,118 --> 01:36:52,487
Ms. Holder, were you at Joe's Drive-In
on the night of June 11, 1963?

1405
01:36:52,690 --> 01:36:53,816
Yes, sir.

1406
01:36:54,024 --> 01:36:57,755
I wasn't working, but I was there
hanging out with my friends.

1407
01:36:58,262 --> 01:37:01,390
T ell the jury if there came
a time when your attention...

1408
01:37:01,599 --> 01:37:04,090
...was directed towards
any particular automobile.

1409
01:37:06,103 --> 01:37:08,833
Being a carhop, you notice cars.

1410
01:37:09,039 --> 01:37:12,202
This one had a long antenna
on the side of it.

1411
01:37:12,409 --> 01:37:14,843
We thought at first
it was a patrol car.

1412
01:37:15,479 --> 01:37:18,448
It was white and it had
a lot of mud on it.

1413
01:37:19,483 --> 01:37:21,280
It was a Plymouth Valiant.

1414
01:37:21,485 --> 01:37:26,252
Mr. Hargrove, were you employed by the
Jackson Police Department in June 1963?

1415
01:37:26,457 --> 01:37:28,186
Yes, I was.

1416
01:37:28,392 --> 01:37:32,123
In charge of the ldentification Division
for 42 years.

1417
01:37:32,329 --> 01:37:35,457
Did you reach a conclusion
as to whose fingerprint...

1418
01:37:35,666 --> 01:37:38,100
...was on the telescopic side
of the gun...

1419
01:37:38,302 --> 01:37:42,568
...recovered in your presence
on June 12, 1963?

1420
01:37:42,907 --> 01:37:44,169
Yes, sir. I did.

1421
01:37:44,375 --> 01:37:47,674
With 14 points of identification,
there's more than enough...

1422
01:37:47,878 --> 01:37:51,211
...to identify the fingerprint
of Mr. Byron De La Beckwith.

1423
01:37:51,515 --> 01:37:55,781
After four days of testimony in the
trial of white supremacist Beckwith...

1424
01:37:55,986 --> 01:37:59,387
...the prosecution, thus far, has
presented essentially the same case...

1425
01:37:59,590 --> 01:38:00,887
...as was offered up
in the two original trials.

1426
01:38:02,826 --> 01:38:05,954
However, this time there are
two significant differences.

1427
01:38:06,163 --> 01:38:08,222
First, the makeup of the jury.

1428
01:38:08,432 --> 01:38:12,562
In 1964, Beckwith faced
two all-male, all-white juries.

1429
01:38:12,770 --> 01:38:16,399
Today, he faces a jury made up
of eight blacks and four whites.

1430
01:38:16,607 --> 01:38:20,737
Tomorrow the prosecution is expected
to introduce three new witnesses...

1431
01:38:20,945 --> 01:38:23,607
... who did not testify
in the first two trials.

1432
01:38:25,783 --> 01:38:27,774
State your name for the record.

1433
01:38:27,985 --> 01:38:29,418
Delmar Dennis.

1434
01:38:29,620 --> 01:38:32,020
Mr. Dennis, in March of 1964...

1435
01:38:32,222 --> 01:38:34,349
...were you a member
of an organization known as...

1436
01:38:34,558 --> 01:38:36,458
...the White Knights
of the Ku Klux Klan?

1437
01:38:36,660 --> 01:38:37,786
I was.

1438
01:38:37,995 --> 01:38:39,519
In September of that year...

1439
01:38:39,730 --> 01:38:42,631
...did you become
a paid informant for the FBl?

1440
01:38:42,833 --> 01:38:44,095
I did.

1441
01:38:44,301 --> 01:38:46,201
And in your capacity as informant...

1442
01:38:46,403 --> 01:38:49,998
...did you ever encounter
the defendant, Byron De La Beckwith?

1443
01:38:50,708 --> 01:38:52,039
I did.

1444
01:38:53,043 --> 01:38:55,477
What were the circumstances
of that encounter?

1445
01:38:56,213 --> 01:38:59,341
On August 8, 1965,
I met Mr. Beckwith...

1446
01:38:59,550 --> 01:39:01,745
